                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1815</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-03T12:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1916, noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In view of probable landing troops here tomorrow which may not be understood in
                    other parts of Republic as being for protection of American Legation, Consulate,
                    American citizens, and in view of the fact that there are in other parts of the
                    country Americans who would be in danger, I request additional ships be sent
                    here with force sufficient to protect American life and property. Puerto Plata,
                    Macorîs, Sanchez should be provided for.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
